$$ \varDelta G=\varDelta H- T\varDelta S=- RT\ln {K}_{\mathrm{A}} $$
\end{document}ΔG=ΔH−TΔS=−RTlnKAwhere ΔG, ΔH, and ΔS are the changes in free energy, enthalpy, and entropy of binding, respectively. T is the absolute temperature and R is the gas constant (8.314 J/mol/K).

Sensorgrams can be utilized for the determination of kinetic parameters, association/dissociation constants (K
A/K
D), on/off rates (k
on/k
